CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 18, 1967, pg. 13 reads: "Star Attraction - The Ramsey Lewis Trio shown in action here, was the star attraction at the Walt Harper Jazz Workshop. Trio includes Ramsey Lewis, pianist; Cleveland Eaton, bassist, and Maurice White, drums.  The group "broke it up" and left the crowd calling for more."
TitMainTitle: Ramsey Lewis band with Ramsey Lewis on piano, Cleveland Eaton on bass, and Maurice White on drums, performing in Hilton Hotel for Walt Harper Jazz Workshop
